title: For Sale:  FOR THOSE WHO SELL 22 AMMO TO MAKE A PROFIT (AS WELL AS 22 HOARDERS)
postcontent:
I hate to bother you but why would you buy ammo and then sell it for more than double the price. I, as well as the rest of the gun community, am getting tired of seeing this happening. People find ammo in their local stores; buy as much of the 22 ammo as they can then post it up for double or even triple the price that they paid. I understand you are trying to make some money, but know you are “steeling" other peoples' money. By steeling I mean whoever buys your ammo could have bought the ammo for less than half the price you are selling it for. There are other people in the shooting community that just want 22 ammo to go shooting. People like you, that try to make money off 22 ammo, are making it difficult for many others. Put yourself in the shoes of those who are trying to buy 22 ammo just so they can go have fun at the range but can’t due to shelves being empty, not a good position to be in. I've been trying to find ammo in stores for a long time but haven’t been able to find any for a long time already. Just know that when you sell ammo to make money off of it you are putting many people in a hard position, as they want to go shooting buy they don’t want to spend twice as much money as if they would at the store. 
A big part of why we are having a shortage of 22 ammo is because of those who buy out all the 22 ammo from stores. If people wouldn't be buying ammo to resell it then many others would be able to get 22 ammo more easily and at a regular price. Because there are those buy 22 ammo just to resell it, is a big reason for the constantly empty shelves in stores. People see 22 ammo so they buy as much as they can because they are worried they won’t be able to find ammo when they will want to go shooting. Please stop selling 22 ammo to make profit. You are making it really hard for others to buy ammo just to go shooting. 

For those who hoard 22 ammo, know that you too are the reason to the "22 ammo shortage".

As for those who are looking for 22 ammo. DO NOT BUY 22 AMMO FROM THOSE WHO ARE SELLING IT TO MAKE PROFIT.
If no one buys 22 ammo from those who sell it for outrageous prices then the sellers will have no reason to buy ammo to resell it. 

Once again, sorry for taking your time but I’m am just getting sick of seeing this happen.

title: For Sale:  Cabela's Tactical Big-Game Riflescope *PENDING SALE*
postcontent:
There have been 30 rounds fired with this optic, i bought a Remington 700 AAC-SD which came with this scope on it. I have to say i have read mixed reviews online, but this glass is very good actually, all the way out to 500 yrd  (which is the longest ive shot with it) the target is very clear. With these scopes, there is no need to guess what the proper hold over on a target is. You simply range your target and dial in the scope for that distance. it might not be the optic i would recommend for the tactical shooter, but for hunting this scope is spot on. This scope is also said to be by cabelas water proof and shock proof, i have not tried this.

I am selling this because im building this rifle into a tactical  weapon, i want to start shooting matched and i would rather have a mildot type optic, but like i said i had no problem hitting metal plates at 500 yards with this scope. but i am selling to fund another scope for my rifle.

Factory new in the box with Para hard case, all packaging (including serial numbered box), manual and one (still sealed) original Para 30 round magazine (uses standard M16/M4 mags).  The Para USA Tactical Target Rifle, TTR-XA is a semi-automatic rifle that’s made in the U.S.A, 5.56mm caliber (can also fire .223 ammo) and features a 16.5" chrome lined barrel, a Rapid Deployment Stock (RDS) (LOP adjustable from 11 3/4" to 14 3/8") and an overall length 34 3/4" to 38" (27 3/4" with stock folded).  One of the great things about this rifle, is the Delayed Impingement Gas System (DIGS), which puts the recoil system up front, above the barrel, which pushes the muzzle back down for quicker follow up shots and reduced felt recoil. Because of the DIGS, the rifle can be fired with the stock folded and the stock locks up nice and tight!  Not only does it have a full length Picatinney rail at the 12 o’clock position and full length forearm rails at the 3, 6 and 9 positions.

The rifle also features a Manifold Injection System (MIS), which expels gases through the bolt carrier, making this the cleanest running auto-loading rifle in the world, plus it can be field stripped with not tools.  These rifles were manufactured by Para USA in Charlotte, NC.  This is the high end model and rarest of the three models Para made. Features a Command Arms Accessories G-27 grip with finger grooves, contoured backstrap and storage compartment.  Made for less than 2 years, but still under full warranty from Para.

“In my experience it does shoot lighter than your average vanilla AR, and my T&E gun was crazy accurate.” – Michael Bane

title: For Sale:  SightMark Ultra Shot QD reflex sight
postcontent:
Used.

This is an ultra shot QD reflex sighting aperture. It appears to be in like new condition.

This comes with original packaging, bikini cover,and built in quick release mount. For those who do not know, they have 5 power levels of brightness, and an off setting, and an option of 4 separate reticle patterns. (That's cross hairs to the non gun enthusiast). This is effectively a clone or copy of an Eotech sight, but at a MUCH more affordable cost. Typically the full retail of these sights are around $139.00 - $149.00 but nobody pays retail for anything anymore... THANKS TO THE INTERNET!! I have found them as cheap as $119.00 with a fair amount of shopping around. So, if you are looking for a sight that does not cost $400.00 or more but has reasonable durability and reasonable battery life (you wont get thousands of hours like an Eotech), then perhaps this is the sight for you.

Alas, this is used, but everything appears to be in good working condition, all of the settings work, all of the 'reticles' work, and of coarse the battery appears to work as well. I would love to charge retail for it and make a few bucks, but used is used. And thus the price reflects a used sight. This is not the fancy new digital auto shutoff model, but the 'old school' turn it off yourself model... so maybe not the sight for you if your lazy and don't like turning things off. Clearly I can not make guarantee's as to the performance as I did not make this optic, nor am I a dealer of them. I did however take some pictures so you could see functionality for yourself. The price of $60.00 for a used sight seems fair.

The top picture is the 3MOA dot, the second is the 60 MOA cross hair, the third is a side view of the sight so you can see the quick disconnect.

I do not have time to be on the phone during the day to make arrangements, and then I am out of town in the evenings, and my cell is a company phone which I can not use for personal business... so please communicate by email. Thank you.
